UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Michael LISENA, Defendant-Appellant. No. 138. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Nov. 3, 1930. D. Joseph De Andrea, of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Frank B. Bozza and George A. Henderson, both of Newark, N. J., of counsel), for appellant. Howard W. Ameli, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y. (Herbert H. Kellogg and Henry G. Singer, Asst. U. S. Attys., both of Brooklyn, N. Y., of counsel), for the United States.

Before MANTON, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
